  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>As it has for over a decade, previously as the State Environmental Protection Administration and since 2008 as the Ministry of Environmental Protection (MEP), China‚Äôs MEP issued its annual ‚ÄúState of the Environment Report‚Äù last week.  In presenting the 2010 report at a press conference on Friday, June 3, Vice Minister Li Ganjie frankly stated that while some environmental indicators ‚Äúkept on turning better‚Äù ‚Äì mainly sulfur dioxide emissions ‚Äì ‚Äúthe overall environmental situation is still very grave and is facing many difficulties and challenges.‚Äù</p></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-view-node">
                <span class="field-content"><div class="readmore"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../china-issues-annual-state-environment-report-ministry-calls-situation-very-grave">Read More</a></div></span>
