                <span class="field-content">April 28, 2011</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p><em>Lawrence Berkeley National Lab researchers present new ‚Äúbottom up‚Äù data</em></p>

<p>A group at Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory, including ChinaFAQs Network Experts,<sup>1</sup> has come out with a new and much more detailed <A href="http://china.lbl.gov/publications/2050-outlook">projection of China‚Äôs energy use and greenhouse gas emissions through 2050</a>.  The result of this more intensive, ‚Äúbottom up‚Äù analysis is good news for global energy security and the climate.  The group‚Äôs projection suggests that Chinese energy use could actually plateau before 2050 and greenhouse emissions could peak between 2025 and 2030.</p></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-view-node">
                <span class="field-content"><div class="readmore"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../new-study-shows-how-chinas-greenhouse-gas-emissions-can-peak-2030">Read More</a></div></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-tid">
